gh":"price[t] / max(price, last 252d) - 1 (how far below the 1-year peak).","dma":"price[t] / mean(price, last N days) - 1; 'above' = price >= the N-day average.","drawdown":"current = price[t]/running-peak - 1; maxDD = min(price/cummax - 1) over the window.","liquidity":"median daily traded value (turnover \u00f7 1e7 = \u20b9 cr) over the last ~21 trading days.","relative_strength":"horizon: stock return - benchmark return (pp); line: (stock/benchmark) rebased to 100 over the last year."},"notes":{"source":"adjusted total-return price panel (bhavcopy-reconstructed) + NSE index TR + bhavcopy turnover.","frequency":"daily","confidence":"high where history is long; flagged low if thin/short.","why_useful":"what the market is saying about the stock \u2014 trend, leadership vs the index/sector, and tradeability.","why_it_can_fail":"corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."}},"business":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"flags":[{"label":"Business quality","value":64.3,"unit":"/100","status":"ok","read":"Average quality (64/100).","meaning":"Composite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":1.0,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"good","read":"1.00\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.03,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.03\u00d7, interest cover 36.5\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":46.71,"unit":"% YoY","status":"good","read":"Profit up 47% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":34.7,"pe_percentile":30.0,"median_pe":38.7,"earnings_yield_pct":2.88,"pb":3.5,"ev_ebitda":22.4,"quality_score":64.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":0.6,"peg":58.35,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 30-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 34.7\u00d7 earnings for ~1% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u224858.35\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[57.86,57.86,57.86,57.86,51.83,51.83,51.83,51.83,51.83,51.83,51.83,51.83],"latest_pct":51.83,"chg_1y_pp":0.0},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[2.8,4.91,4.05,3.59,6.88,4.48,5.04,6.9,7.39,7.9,7.58,7.29],"latest_pct":7.29,"chg_1y_pp":0.39},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[23.38,22.45,24.17,25.23,32.83,35.37,34.8,33.27,32.86,32.63,32.99,33.36],"latest_pct":33.36,"chg_1y_pp":0.09},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[15.97,14.78,13.93,13.32,8.46,8.33,8.33,8.0,7.93,7.63,7.62,7.52],"latest_pct":7.52,"chg_1y_pp":-0.48}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"16-Aug-2024","subject":"Annual General Meeting/Dividend - Rs 20 Per Share","materiality":"Low"},{"date":"14-Aug-2025","subject":"Dividend - Rs 18 Per Share","materiality":"Low"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disclosures","note":"promoter & designated-person dealings \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Exchange announcements","note":"NSE/BSE filings stream \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Results calendar","note":"next board-meeting / results date \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Credit ratings","note":"rating-agency actions \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."}],"reads":{"Promoter":"Promoter stake stable at 51.83%.","FII":"FIIs adding (+0.39pp YoY \u2192 7.29%).","DII":"DIIs adding (+0.09pp YoY \u2192 33.36%)."},"meaning":"Quarterly shareholding (% held by Promoters / Foreign (FII) / Domestic (DII) institutions / Public) from Screener, plus exchange corporate actions tagged by materiality (High = structural: bonus/split/buyback/merger; Low = routine: dividend/AGM).","why_useful":"Rising promoter & institutional ownership and clean corporate actions are confirming signals; falling promoter stake or pledging is a governance/skin-in-the-game warning.","why_it_can_fail":"Shareholding is a lagged quarterly snapshot; promoter % can fall for benign reasons (QIP, ESOP dilution). Pledge & insider detail are deferred (placeholders below)."},"snapshot":{"dimensions":{"Market":{"verdict":"positive","score":3,"drivers":["+ Trades above its 200-day average (+23%).","+ 50-day average above the 200-day (golden cross).","+ Within 2% of its 52-week high.","+ Outpacing the NIFTY 500 by +30pp over 12 months.","\u2212 In a deep drawdown (-46% from its peak)."],"rule":"Points: +1 price above its 200-day average \u00b7 +1 a golden cross (50-day \u2265 200-day) \u00b7 +1 within 10% of the 52-week high \u00b7 +1 beating the NIFTY 500 over 12 months; \u22121 for each opposite, and \u22121 if more than 25% below its peak. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less, otherwise neutral."},"Business":{"verdict":"positive","score":3,"drivers":["\u00b7 Average quality (64/100).","+ 1.00\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","+ Conservatively financed (D/E 0.03\u00d7, interest cover 36.5\u00d7).","+ Profit up 47% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating."],"rule":"Points across the four business flags: +1 for each that is 'good' (quality, cash conversion, balance-sheet safety, earnings momentum), \u22121 for each that is 'weak'. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less."},"Valuation":{"verdict":"neutral","score":0,"drivers":["\u00b7 P/E at the 30-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."],"rule":"Cheap \u2014 P/E below the 30th percentile of its own 10-year range \u2014 scores +2 (supportive); expensive (above the 70th) scores \u22122; mid-range is 0. A peak/cyclical-earnings flag discounts a cheap read to +1. NOTE: 'positive' means the multiple looks supportive vs the stock's OWN history \u2014 it is NOT a buy call."},"Ownership":{"verdict":"neutral","score":0,"drivers":[],"rule":"Points: +1 promoter stake rising \u00b7 \u22121 promoter stake falling more than 1pp in a year \u00b7 \u22121 promoter pledge above 10% \u00b7 +1 for each of FII / DII accumulating (>0.5pp in a year). Verdict: positive at +1 or more, negative at \u22121 or less."}},"top_positives":["Trades above its 200-day average (+23%).","50-day average above the 200-day (golden cross).","Within 2% of its 52-week high.","Outpacing the NIFTY 500 by +30pp over 12 months.","1.00\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","Conservatively financed (D/E 0.03\u00d7, interest cover 36.5\u00d7)."],"key_risks":["In a deep drawdown (-46% from its peak)."],"monitor_next":["Next quarterly results (board-meeting date is an MVP-2 placeholder).","Re-rating toward / away from its median P/E (38.7\u00d7).","Relative-strength inflection vs its sector index.","Promoter pledge / institutional-holding changes next quarter."],"caveats":["corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."],"confidence":"high","disclaimer":"Diagnostics only \u2014 a structured reading of price behaviour, business fundamentals, valuation and ownership for your OWN judgement. This is NOT a buy/sell/hold recommendation.","method":"Each dimension is a transparent points tally of the named signals listed beneath it \u2014 open a dimension to see the exact signals that fired and its rule. Verdict = positive at